metadata.name: Pensado a mano #444
metadata.description:
WARNING: Read instructions so you don‚Äôt get a broken token!!
----


Q: Why haven‚Äôt you tried fx(params)?
A: Pff.. Sliders?


‚ÄúPensado a mano‚Äù explores the intersection of Generative Art and Hand Drawing. The collector, by drawing a predefined number of shapes on canvas, creates a unique hand-crafted seed that generates the final artwork. That is the only customisable param, thought by hand, which interacts with various random attributes to produce a unique composition.

‚Äú‚Ä¶the time we spend doing and making things, the process‚Ä¶‚Äù

And yet the process continues. On the background, the code generates a plottable svg.
An artificially extended process, from hand to screen, from screen to paper, that creates a new kind of mixed media.

Signed plots will soon be claimable via Artfora (tbd price + shipping)


INSTRUCTIONS

1 - Draw the requested shapes and wait to see the result. You can change the Seed Nr. slider if you don't like the selected mode.
2 - Press ‚ÄúC‚Äù to copy drawing to Clipboard
3 - Copy the clipboard contents to the text-input on the fx(params) sidebar

***Important. If you buy several tickets, make sure you don't mint the same Seed Nr. twice (slider)

press ‚ÄúS‚Äù to save the PNG, press ‚ÄúP‚Äù to plot the SVG


DISCLAIMER

This is a high-supply token minted during a bear market. Have Fun.

metadata.name: Crystal Alpha #8
metadata.description:
This project uses L-Systems to create crystalline forms and fx(params) allows minters control the final results - experiment to to see what you can create!


Parameters

Palette - a choice of several palettes
Color Control - experiment with this -it affects the way the crystal makes use of the palette
BG Color Control - similar to above, but for the background
Spins - the number of rotations used to form the crystal
Opacity - Opacity for the crystal
Opacity - Opacity for the background
Object Scale - Adjust the crystal object size
Back Scale - Adjust the background size
BG Angle - The angle used to render the background - experiment to see different effects
Iterations - Determines the number of L-System iterations are use to render the crystal
Circle - If set, a circle is drawn behind the crystal
Curve Vertex - If set, curve vertex is used instead of regular vertex.

Random Seed - This overrides the fxhash seed so what you see after setting all parameters is what you'll get when you mint. When using params this value is initially seeded using the fxhash seed so it is highly unlikely that two mints would be identical

Ink wash painting is a type of Chinese ink brush painting which uses black ink, such as that used in Chinese calligraphy, in different concentrations.
In landscape painting the scenes depicted are typically imaginary, or very loose adaptations of actual views.
-
All made with p5js

metadata.name: a fleeting moment #80
metadata.description:
Abstract expressionism always has been, and always will be, my first love. With this piece, the initial premise was "can I write a bit of code that will render images in the style that I actually paint in real life?" 

It took several full days of poking and prodding, and I departed from the original mission once I had what I was looking for, but in general, I think I succeeded. My wife was looking over my shoulder at one point, and thought I was looking at a scan of one of my actual paintings, which sounds like success to me. 

Created with love in p5.js

metadata.name: Finestre #278
metadata.description:
"Finestre" means windows or apertures in Italian. This generative art project was inspired by the appreciation of collected memories, windows in time to our past experiences and loved ones. Using basic geometry such as rectangles, squares, circles, ellipses, triangles with random compositions and many possible color palettes, Finestre presents our impression of portals to the Universes of collected memories through abstract still code-based outputs.

Finestre is a collaboration generative art project between generative artists Gonz0x and Schizzo.

Finestre has some fun interactive features which allows collectors to view the work in different configurations. For example, collectors can isolate the deconstructed background layers, isolate the main constructed layer, add Grain and also enter a Free Play mode which allows for the option to draw background and foreground layers, stacking infinitely. You can Save off a render as a .png.

Press "C" for Constructed Mode (Isolate Foreground)
Press "D" for Deconstructed Mode (Isolate Background)
Press "R" to reset to Default = C & D
Press "G" to add grain texture with each press
Press "S" saves render
 
Press "F" to toggle Free Play mode
In Free Play, Press "Q" repeatedly to add Deconstructed layers
In Free Play, Press "W" repeatedly to add Constructed layers

metadata.name: Boom_fx_max #173
metadata.description:
Boom_fx_max, by Stephen Boyd  
August, 2022  
Little India, Toronto, Canada.

This is a free mint for anyone who is a holder of Boom_fx as of August 31, 2022, 00:11:00Z. 

Signed 18" x 12" or 12" x 12" prints are available to holders for both Boom_fx and Boom_fx_max tokens on request. Please send a DM for more information.

Any unclaimed reserves will be released after four days and available at a price to be determined. 


Project Description
---
Boom_fx_max uses all eleven days of data in one image. This constitutes 4,567 earthquakes being represented in every output. This differs from the original Boom_fx which used hours of time on one of the eleven days and typically included a few hundred seismic events.

There are eleven new colour palettes and seven different ratios to organize relationships between visual elements.

The earthquake data comes from the USGS API. There is further documentation (./documentation/Information_about_boom_fx_max.md) included with this project that outlines how this data was collected and the information included in these feeds.


Three Features
---
1. Aspect ratios:
   - Landscape
   - Portrait
   - Square
2. Eleven colour palettes
3. Seven Organizing Principle Ratios:
   - Super Golden Ratio
   - PHI
   - Golden Angle
   - Silver Ratio
   - Euler's Number
   - Reciprocal Fibonacci Constant
   - Feigenbaum Constant


Interaction
---
Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press t: thumbnail @ a maximum pixel width or height of 200px
- Press s: your current screen size
- Press p: print size @ a maximum pixel width or height of 4800px which is 16"@300dpi
- Press h: HD4K on the vertical @ a maximum pixel width or height of 2160px
- Press m: Max size @ a maximum pixel width or height of 10800px.

The filename will include some metadata such as the unique hash, date and time at time of capture.


Appreciation
---
Thank you to everyone who has collected one my pieces.

Thank you to the USGS for making this data available.

And thank you the most to KIRH.


Data Sources, Software Libraries and VCS / Source Code
--- 
Data Sources
All earthquake data is sourced from the USGS Earthquake API for the International Federation of Digital Seismograph Networks (FDSN). 

Software Libraries Used
Made with Processing / P5.js  
p5.js v1.4.1 February 02, 2022

metadata.name: Morse me #15
metadata.description:
Meta level
'Morse me' can be a call. It can just as well be sarcasm and irony about today's time, where technology should actually connect people more, but it makes them partly lonely. It also describes the artist himself.
Anyway, it's pretty cool to combine an old technology like morse code with a current one to generate art. To honor the inventor of the morse code, the release date was set to his birthday.

Technical
The parameters affect the direction of how the finished output will look and is intended to give the collector customization options so that the output is not a complete surprise. Nevertheless, there are randomly generated values which make it very unlikely to generate an exactly identical image, even though at minimum and maximum values the differences are minor and hardly detectable. As a result, images can appear the same.

Randomness
Words used in the word collection to generate the morse code and thus the pattern are chosen randomly.
A word consists of letters, a letter is in turn described by a morse code, which consists of single characters. It is randomly generated whether spaces are inserted between words, letters and characters (feature).
The roundness of the rectangles in mode Rec can take up to three different combinations, which are also chosen randomly (feature). 
For the layers in mode Rec, there are combinations where the layers can be rotated depending on their number. The combinations are chosen randomly.

Interactions
[s] save
[l] save large resolution
[u] save ultra resolution
[F12] to see the used words in the used order in the console, which were used for the morse code and generated the pattern

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of Fran√ßois Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #80
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. ‚ÄúThe Bugged Tree‚Äù‚Äôs code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren‚Äôt under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there‚Äôs a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Mecha-Bamboo #66
metadata.description:
Mecha-Bamboo is the second installment in the Mecha series, where I attempt to blend mechanical elements with nature.

The main building blocks used in this piece are metal pipes, nuts and bolts forming bamboo stems and mending plates extending outwards with sharp metal scraps at their ends resembling branches and leaves. 

There are 4 main arrangement variations 
	- Two abstract variations with the metal bamboos growing out of the sides and border (20% chance each)
	- Two landscape arrangements, one on flat planes and the other on floating platforms.  (30% chance each)

The dominant stroke and fill colors are chosen at random from the RGB color space and are only recomputed if certain contrast criteria aren't fulfilled. 
In combination with one of 10 hand-selected color palettes used for accents, this allows a great variation of different possible color schemes.

The structure and appearance of the bamboo, its stems and leaves are controlled by over 50 parameters that are chosen at random, giving each iteration a unique style.



Keys: 
S - Save PNG image
V - Open SVG Export menu
Space - Pause

Plotting:
You can export a plottable SVG of each iteration by opening the export menu. I plot these on A3 with a 0.1mm fineliner. But depending on the density of the iteration other choices might be better suited. 


The image is generated entirely in Javascript and the postprocessing is done with a custom shader. If there is no webgl support, the image will render without any postprocessing. You can force this by appending the URL parameter "?noWebgl=1".

Libraries used:
Three.js & EffectComposer
Javascript-Voronoi by gorhill
perlin.js by  Joseph Gentle
dat.gui
